                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1438">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/394.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Vice
                        Consul <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Spanish Embassy reports Constitutionalists at San Luis Potosi are exacting loans
                    from Spanish residents there and are confiscating their cattle.</p>
                <p>Request Carranza to telegraph orders to local authorities at San Luis Potosi to
                    discontinue enforcing unjust loans and to return confiscated property to
                    rightful owners.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
